    "transliteration": "DUA AL MAHDI\r\n\r\nThe Supplication of Imam al-Mahdi (a.s.):\r\n\r\nAl-Kaf’ami, in al-Misbah, says “This is the supplicatory prayer of Imam al-Mahdi (a.s.):\r\n\r\nBISMILLAHIR RAHMANIR RAHEEM ALLAAHUMMAR ZUQNAA TAWFEEQAT TAA-A'TE WA BO'DAL MA'SEYATE WA SIDQAN NIYYATE WA I'RFAANAL HURMATE WA AKRIMNAA BIL HODAA WAL ISTEQAAMATE WA SADDID ALSENATANAA BIS SAWAABE WAL HIKMATE WAM-LAA QOLOOBANAA BIL I'LME WAL MA'REFATE WA TAHHIR BOTOONANAA MENAL HARAAME WASH-SHUBHATE WAK-FUF AYDEYANAA A'NIZ ZULME WAS SAREQATE WAGH-ZUZ ABSAARANAA A'NIL FOJOORE WAL KHEYAANATE WAS-DUD ASMAA-A'NAA A'NIL LAGHWE WAL GHEEBATE WA TAFAZZAL A'LAA O'LAMAAA-ENAA BIZ ZOHDE WAN NASEEHATE WA A'LAL MOTA-A'LLEMEENA BIL JOHDE WAR-RAGHBATE WA A'LAL MUSTAME-E'ENA BIL ITTEBAA-E' WAL MAW-E'ZATE WA A'LAA MARZAL MUSLEMEENA BISH-SHE-FAAA-E WAR RAAHATE WA A'LAA MAWTAAHUM BIR-RAAFATE WAR-RAHMATE WA A'LAA MASHAA-YEKHENAA BIL WAQAARE WAS-SAKINATE WA A'LASH SHABAABE BIL ENAABATE WAT TAWBATE WA A'LAN NESAAA-E BIL HAYAAA-E WAL I'FFATE WA A'LAL AGHNEYAAA-E BIT TAWAA-ZO-E' WAS SA-A'TE WA A'LAL FOQARAAA-E BIS SABRE WAL QANAA-A'TE WA A'LAL GHOZAATE BIN NASRE WAL GHALABATE WA A'LAL OSARAAA-E BIL KHALAASE WAR-RAAHATE WA A'LAL OMARAAA-E BIL A'DLE WASH-SHAFAQATE WA A'LAR RA-E'EYYATE BIL INSAAFE WA HUSNIS SEERATE WA BAARIK LIL-HUJJAAJE WAZ-ZUWWAARE FIZ-ZAADE WAN-NAFAQATE WAQZE MAA AWJABTA A'LAYHIM MENAL HAJJE WAL-U'MRATE BE FAZLEKA WA RAHMATEKA YAA ARHAMAR RAAHEMEEN.", 
    "english": "DUA AL MAHDI\r\n\r\nThe Supplication of Imam al-Mahdi (a.s.):\r\n\r\nAl-Kaf’ami, in al-Misbah, says “This is the supplicatory prayer of Imam al-Mahdi (a.s.):\r\n\r\nO Allah, (please do) grant us success to obey (You), remoteness from disobedience (to You), true intention, and identification of sanctity. (Please do) honor us with true guidance and straightforwardness, dedicate our tongues to truth and wisdom, fill our hearts with knowledge and learning, purify our stomachs from illegally and suspiciously gotten food, withhold our hands from oppression and larceny, turn our sights away from licentiousness and treachery, and block our hearings against vainness and backbiting, confer upon our scholars with asceticism and advice, upon the learners with hard work and desire (to learning), upon the listeners with following and learning (lessons), upon the Muslim patients with cure and comfort, upon the dead Muslims with kindness and mercy, upon our aged people with somberness and gentleness, upon the youths with turning (to You) and repentance, upon the women with shyness and chastity, upon the rich with modesty and ample giving, upon the poor with patience and satisfaction, upon the warriors with triumph and supremacy, upon the prisoners with release and comfort, upon the rulers with justice and sympathy, and upon the subjects with impartiality and good behavior. (Please do) bless the pilgrims to Mecca and the visitors (of the tombs of the saints) with provision and expenditure, and help them settle the Hajj and 'Umrah that You have made incumbent upon them, in the name of Your grace and mercy, O most merciful of all those who show mercy! "
}